== Fundamentals of Vector Fields 

#definition[
  A vector field describes how each point on the plane corresponds to a vector. Formally, $ vb(F) = m vu(i) + n vu(j), $ where $m$ and $n$ are dependent on $(x, y)$. 
]

Vector fields are incredibly useful in many sciences including mechanics, electricity & magnetism, thermodynamics, geography, meteorology, etc. 
